description: DNO ASA engages in the exploration, development, and production of oil and gas assets in the Middle East, the North Sea, and West Africa. The company holds75% operating interests in the Tawke and Peshkabir fields located in the Kurdistan; and 9% interest in CÃ´te d'Ivoire's Block CI-27 located in West Africa. It also holds licenses in reservoirs, including in the Cretaceous, Jurassic and Triassic formations; and 85 offshore licenses in Norway, seven offshore licenses in the UK, and one offshore license in the Netherlands. DNO ASA was formerly known as DNO International ASA and changed its name to DNO ASA in June 2014. The company was incorporated in 1971 and is headquartered in Oslo, Norway.
